<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">RECITALS&nbsp;</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>WHEREAS; </strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">the Company provides an online platform enabling the general public to place orders for meal preparation;&nbsp;</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>WHEREAS; </strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">the Service Provider provides meal preparation services in the territory from where such orders originate;</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>&nbsp;WHEREAS;</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"> the Company wishes to provide access to the Service Provider for fulfilment of such orders;&nbsp;</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>WHEREAS;</strong><span style="font-weight: 400;"> the Service Provider wishes to fulfill orders for such orders;</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>NOWTHEREFORE, </strong><span style="font-weight: 400;">in consideration of the promises and other good and valuable consideration, &nbsp; the sufficiency and receipt of which are hereby acknowledged, the parties agree as follows:</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br /></span><strong>1. </strong><strong>GOPREP SERVICES</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">1.1&nbsp; &nbsp; </span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">GoPrep provides access to Customers (who may consist of consumers, organizations or companies or any third parties) expressing interest in meal preparation services (&ldquo;Service Requests&rdquo;).&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">1.2&nbsp; &nbsp; </span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">GoPrep may send you a communication regarding a Customer&rsquo;s Service Request that contains information about what service has been requested and customer&rsquo;s contact information (an &ldquo;Order&ldquo;).&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">1.3&nbsp; &nbsp; </span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Orders will be sent to you based on the information you submit during your creation of a Company Profile on the GoPrep website.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">1.4&nbsp; &nbsp; </span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">We do not guarantee to provide you with any specific number of Orders, nor do we provide any guarantees, representations or warranties regarding a customer's level of interest, their desire to have services completed, their ability to pay you, the accuracy of the information provided by the customers, or that any customers will hire you to perform services, nor do we guarantee that you will successfully contact each customer.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">1.5&nbsp; &nbsp; </span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">We are not involved in, nor do we have any responsibility for your contracts with customers, their creditworthiness, or any payments to you or any disputes they may have with you or you may have with them. Company is free to contract with other Service Providers as this is not an exclusive contract.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<ul>
<li><strong><strong>2. SERVICE PROVIDER SERVICES</strong></strong></li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">2.1&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Representations and Warranties. You represent and warrant that you have all requisite power and authority to enter into this Agreement and to sell the goods or provide the services which are the subject of the Service; where applicable, you are legally and properly licensed to and possesses all requisite licenses and permits to complete the Services in the geographic areas in which the work is located.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">2.2&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; </span> <span style="font-weight: 400;">Liability Coverage. You have a valid policy of liability insurance (in coverage amounts consistent with all applicable legal requirements) that names or schedules you for the operation of the Services and the coverage of all damages that can incur while you are performing the Services.</span></p>
<ul>
<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;"><br /></span><strong>3. </strong><strong>PRICING</strong><strong>.</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">3.1 Customer payments (the &ldquo;Payments&rdquo;) shall be collected by the Company and processed via a gateway of our choosing which is currently Stripe. The Customer may also opt in to process payments with their preferred gateway for an additional monthly fee.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">3.2 The Company fee is a percentage based on an aforementioned agreement between the Company and the Service Provider based on the gross order amount, minus the processing and shipping fees. There is an additional two and nine-tenth percent (2.9%) and .30 cents credit card processing fee per transaction if the Customer is using the standard Stripe Connect payment processing.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">3.3 100% minus 2.9% and .30 cents plus the transaction fee percentage agreed upon by the Company and the Service Provider shall be paid to Service Provider at the time of payment by the customer.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">3.4 Pricing is subject to change at the discretion of the Company upon sixty (60) days&rsquo; written notice to Service Provider.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">3.5 The Customer may also choose to pay a flat monthly fee based on the amount of monthly orders collected, with no additional percentage per transaction with the exception of credit card processing fees from Stripe or the Customer&rsquo;s preferred payment processor. Flat monthly fees are billed automatically from the Customer&rsquo;s connected Stripe account balance per month or with a provided credit card that will be kept on file.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">3.6 A Customer may also choose to pay a flat rate for any extended period of time, such as three months, six months, or one year. In this case the Customer must pay the agreed upon amount at the commencement of the contract for access to the Service Provider&rsquo;s platform for the agreed upon amount of time. The Customer will be charged recurringly after the agreed upon duration of time has expired. Any cancellation of services before the duration has expired does not warrant a refund.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">3.7 For cancellation of services, the Customer must contact their sales representative or </span><a href="mailto:support@goprep.com"><span style="font-weight: 400;">support@goprep.com</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;"> before their scheduled charge date has renewed.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">3.8 Sales Tax. GoPrep automatically determines each store's state sales tax based on an external node module integrated from npmjs.com. Each store on our&nbsp; platform has the ability to override this automatically determined rate with their own rate as well as remove the sales tax rate entirely. GoPrep is not responsible or liable for any discrepancies involving the incorrect use of sales tax as set by the store if the store decides to override the automatically determined rate. Store&rsquo;s are responsible for reporting their proper sales tax documents to the IRS and for paying all taxes that are due.&nbsp;</span></p>
